						<summary>

						<p>Stone fixed into the sluice of the tank called Nāyani-<hi rend="italic">Cheruvu.</hi></p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1095, Rudhirōdgāri, Vaiśākha śu. Ēkādaśi.</hi> [Though the week-day is not mentined it is A.D. date to be given <hi rend="bold">April 25, Wednesday.</hi> The cyclic year was Vijaya.]</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to records a gift of land by Kāḷama-nāyaka to some <hi rend="italic">brāhmaṇas</hi> as an <hi rend="italic">agrahāra</hi> for the merit of his parents. The donor is stated to be the sarvant <hi rend="italic">(baṇṭu)</hi> of Paṇṭa Nalla-siddhirāju. Vijādēva-mahārāja is mentioned as the ruler.</p>						

						</summary>
